text_Original: To answer the question about translation of the experience to 2D, least for me it's pretty clear how incredible it must be in the VR experience, having used VR devices myself. Lex's opinion that it has crossed the "uncanny valley" is pretty bold and likely not uttered lightly. Clearly a transformative technology, regardless of what applications actually flourish with it. I did have to roll my eyes a bit at the Zuckerberg's groupware/collab aspirations. A new groupware paradigm or even just successful app is one of those unicorns that everyone has been chasing since the invention of email and the road is littered with hundreds if not thousands of failed brilliant ideas. This tech could find a place in that space but there's a long way to go before it's more productive than intrusive. Time will tell.
